      biography:
        'She was born on June 21, 1965 in Chicago (Illinois, USA) in the family of a nurse and a Polish businessman.\n\nIs a trans woman. Lana Wachowski came out as a transgender woman in July 2012, becoming the first openly transgender person among major Hollywood directors. In October 2012, the human rights organization Human Rights Campaign celebrated the courage of coming out with the Visibility Award.\n\nAfter graduating from school, she entered Bard College in New York, but soon left her studies and returned home, where she and her sister went into construction business. In 1994, they wrote the first script for the film “Assassins” (1995), but asked to remove their names from the credits due to disagreements with the director, who almost completely rewrote the plot of the story.\n\nIn 1996, the directorial debut of the Wachowski sisters (at that time brothers) - the thriller "Connection" - was released. One of the most famous works of the creative duo was the Matrix film series, which won fans around the world.',
